1
00:01:12,205 --> 00:01:13,604
Taiwan is located along the

2
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:14,966
boundary of the Pacific Ocean

3
00:01:15,208 --> 00:01:17,677
and the Eurasian continent.

4
00:01:17,911 --> 00:01:19,970
It is also the largest island

5
00:01:20,213 --> 00:01:21,942
along the Tropic of Cancer.

6
00:01:23,183 --> 00:01:26,153
While most countries along

7
00:01:26,386 --> 00:01:28,912
the Tropic of Cancer are desert regions,

8
00:01:44,304 --> 00:01:46,466
Taiwan is rich in vegetation

9
00:01:46,707 --> 00:01:49,972
with subtropical and tropical climates.

10
00:01:50,210 --> 00:01:51,644
Taiwan is thus paradise

11
00:01:51,878 --> 00:01:53,607
to many plants and animals.

12
00:01:58,952 --> 00:01:59,612
Moreover,

13
00:01:59,853 --> 00:02:01,116
people from faraway lands

14
00:02:01,355 --> 00:02:03,619
and mainland China crossed

15
00:02:03,857 --> 00:02:04,790
Taiwan Strait and arrived on the island

16
00:02:05,025 --> 00:02:07,016
during different periods.

17
00:02:07,260 --> 00:02:09,490
As a result, the island

18
00:02:09,730 --> 00:02:11,664
features culture as diverse

19
00:02:11,898 --> 00:02:13,832
as its fauna and flora.

20
00:02:18,372 --> 00:02:19,931
The ecology and geology in Taiwan

21
00:02:20,173 --> 00:02:22,073
are rich and diverse,

22
00:02:22,309 --> 00:02:25,301
yet nature also delivers calamities.

23
00:02:25,545 --> 00:02:27,138
Typhoons in summer bring

24
00:02:27,381 --> 00:02:30,078
floods and strong winds.

25
00:02:30,450 --> 00:02:32,885
Earthquakes also cause

26
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:35,680
huge damage and deform the island,

27
00:02:35,922 --> 00:02:37,219
resulting in structural changes

28
00:02:37,457 --> 00:02:39,687
to Taiwan's topography and landforms.

29
00:02:43,363 --> 00:02:45,491
Due to natural and artificial disasters,

30
00:02:45,732 --> 00:02:46,790
people coming to and from

31
00:02:47,034 --> 00:02:48,559
the island have developed

32
00:02:48,802 --> 00:02:49,769
a unique quality

33
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:51,630
for being resilient.

34
00:02:57,411 --> 00:02:57,900
Sometimes

35
00:02:58,145 --> 00:03:00,614
the people are resigned to adversities.

36
00:03:01,615 --> 00:03:04,209
Yet when they are determined to resist,

37
00:03:04,918 --> 00:03:07,410
they show indomitable fighting spirit

38
00:03:07,654 --> 00:03:10,123
in creating new opportunities.

39
00:03:11,491 --> 00:03:13,289
The cycle of destruction and construction

40
00:03:13,527 --> 00:03:16,929
makes Taiwan an island of miracle.

41
00:03:47,327 --> 00:03:49,352
When the Earth was still young,

42
00:03:49,596 --> 00:03:51,030
the island of Taiwan

43
00:03:51,264 --> 00:03:52,732
began to take shape

44
00:03:52,966 --> 00:03:55,128
over 100 million years ago.

45
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:09,374
Some 65 million years ago

46
00:04:09,616 --> 00:04:11,084
during the late Cretaceous Period

47
00:04:11,318 --> 00:04:13,480
when dinosaurs became extinct

48
00:04:17,524 --> 00:04:18,958
the Eurasian Plate

49
00:04:19,192 --> 00:04:21,957
and the Philippine Plate

50
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:24,424
gradually converged.

51
00:04:24,664 --> 00:04:26,860
The early forms of Taiwan's topography

52
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:29,592
took shape during that time.

53
00:04:29,836 --> 00:04:31,702
But still, the island of Taiwan

54
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:34,100
remained submerged.

55
00:04:44,050 --> 00:04:46,542
It was not until 20 million years ago,

56
00:04:46,787 --> 00:04:49,757
that the South China Sea Plate
subducted eastward

57
00:04:49,990 --> 00:04:53,324
under the Philippine Plate,

58
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:55,528
thus forming a volcanic island arc

59
00:04:55,762 --> 00:04:58,925
on the Philippine Plate.

60
00:05:03,904 --> 00:05:05,065
Meanwhile,

61
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:06,272
the Philippine Plate was moving

62
00:05:06,506 --> 00:05:08,474
in a northwestern direction

63
00:05:08,708 --> 00:05:11,200
at a speed of 10 centimeters per year.

64
00:05:15,148 --> 00:05:16,013
Stress resulting from

65
00:05:16,249 --> 00:05:18,149
plate compression peaked

66
00:05:18,385 --> 00:05:21,480
10 million years ago.

67
00:05:22,055 --> 00:05:25,025
During a massive volcanic eruption,

68
00:05:25,258 --> 00:05:27,590
the Penghu islands was raised

69
00:05:27,828 --> 00:05:31,924
from under the sea by lavas.

70
00:05:34,534 --> 00:05:35,899
Six million years ago,

71
00:05:36,136 --> 00:05:38,969
during the period of Penglai Orogeny,

72
00:05:39,206 --> 00:05:40,731
the Philippine Sea Plate and

73
00:05:40,974 --> 00:05:44,035
the Eurasia Plate collided.

74
00:05:45,412 --> 00:05:47,039
The arc-continent collision

75
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:48,645
started the merging of coastal mountains

76
00:05:48,882 --> 00:05:51,112
and the island of Taiwan,

77
00:05:51,351 --> 00:05:54,787
which gradually emerged from the sea.

78
00:06:00,093 --> 00:06:01,720
Fifty thousand years ago,

79
00:06:01,962 --> 00:06:04,226
the volcanic arc at the eastern coast

80
00:06:04,464 --> 00:06:07,798
was merged with the island.

81
00:06:11,438 --> 00:06:13,202
Pushed to the surface,

82
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:15,602
the volcanic arc merged with

83
00:06:15,842 --> 00:06:17,367
the central mountain range
on the Taiwan main island.

84
00:06:18,578 --> 00:06:19,178
These two mountains,

85
00:06:19,179 --> 00:06:21,671
which were located on different plates,

86
00:06:21,915 --> 00:06:25,010
became parts of the Taiwan island.

87
00:06:29,589 --> 00:06:32,058
High mountains,

88
00:06:32,292 --> 00:06:33,726
plains,

89
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:35,450
valleys, and river terrace

90
00:06:35,695 --> 00:06:37,686
thus emerged in Taiwan.

91
00:07:18,571 --> 00:07:21,871
For over one million years,

92
00:07:22,108 --> 00:07:25,100
glacial periods appeared periodically.

93
00:07:25,545 --> 00:07:26,774
The glaciers caused the sea surface

94
00:07:27,013 --> 00:07:28,981
to drop over 140 meters.

95
00:07:38,525 --> 00:07:39,788
Since the average depth of the Taiwan Strait

96
00:07:40,026 --> 00:07:41,892
was only 80 meters,

97
00:07:43,129 --> 00:07:45,120
land masses linked to mainland China

98
00:07:45,365 --> 00:07:48,130
thus appeared during the glacial periods.

99
00:07:54,607 --> 00:07:56,598
Many animals south of the mainland

100
00:07:56,843 --> 00:07:58,333
crossed these land bridges to

101
00:07:58,578 --> 00:08:01,309
the swamp lands in Taiwan for survival.

102
00:08:02,549 --> 00:08:05,951
These included ancient Chinese rhinos,

103
00:08:06,186 --> 00:08:08,314
Chinese Stegodon elephants,

104
00:08:08,555 --> 00:08:10,546
as well as species of bulls,

105
00:08:10,790 --> 00:08:12,417
wild boars and crocodiles.

106
00:08:12,692 --> 00:08:15,627
Ancestors of the Formosan rock monkey

107
00:08:15,862 --> 00:08:18,991
and Formosan black bear
appeared during this period.

108
00:09:05,211 --> 00:09:08,340
This was the Taiwan Strait today.

109
00:09:08,581 --> 00:09:11,710
It was a grassy plain
during the glacial period,

110
00:09:12,052 --> 00:09:14,350
and was referred to as Penghu Channel.

111
00:09:15,288 --> 00:09:17,086
Forty-four thousand years ago,

112
00:09:17,791 --> 00:09:19,156
this herd of ancient moose

113
00:09:19,392 --> 00:09:21,258
migrated to the old Min River area

114
00:09:21,494 --> 00:09:24,395
to escape the severe cold in the north.

115
00:09:24,831 --> 00:09:26,390
As they passed along the river,

116
00:09:26,633 --> 00:09:29,762
they discovered a big grassy plain

117
00:09:30,003 --> 00:09:31,129
along with other creatures

118
00:09:31,371 --> 00:09:33,999
from northern China.

119
00:09:35,375 --> 00:09:38,037
This group of hunters from faraway

120
00:09:38,278 --> 00:09:39,746
might have become the earliest

121
00:09:39,979 --> 00:09:41,970
humans to inhabit the island of Taiwan.

122
00:10:20,587 --> 00:10:22,817
This is present-day Changpin Township
in Taitung County.

123
00:10:23,056 --> 00:10:25,320
The scenic Pahsien Caves

124
00:10:29,596 --> 00:10:30,757
are almost as old as

125
00:10:30,997 --> 00:10:33,125
the Upper Caveman in China.

126
00:10:33,800 --> 00:10:35,063
Fifteen thousand years ago

127
00:10:35,301 --> 00:10:37,827
in the sea-eroded caves
along Taiwan's east coast,

128
00:10:38,171 --> 00:10:41,038
there lived humans in the Paleolithic Age.

129
00:10:42,041 --> 00:10:45,238
They were the Changpin culture people.

130
00:11:07,500 --> 00:11:08,626
They are performing

131
00:11:08,868 --> 00:11:11,166
one of the most ancient survival skills:

132
00:11:12,472 --> 00:11:13,769
fishing.

133
00:11:14,007 --> 00:11:15,031
To hunt,

134
00:11:15,275 --> 00:11:17,573
they needed tools.

135
00:11:18,845 --> 00:11:20,074
The egg-shaped stones on the beach

136
00:11:20,313 --> 00:11:21,838
thus became the most popular material

137
00:11:22,081 --> 00:11:24,277
used by this group of prehistoric humans.

138
00:11:26,152 --> 00:11:27,677
In addition to stone tools,

139
00:11:27,921 --> 00:11:29,821
man during the Paleolithic Age

140
00:11:30,056 --> 00:11:32,047
also hunted animals for food

141
00:11:33,326 --> 00:11:33,849
and were adept at using

142
00:11:34,093 --> 00:11:36,187
animal bones and skins

143
00:11:36,429 --> 00:11:38,659
to take care of their tribesmen.

144
00:11:39,599 --> 00:11:42,091
Abundant environmental resources

145
00:11:42,335 --> 00:11:45,327
also facilitated the survival
of the Changpin people.

146
00:11:46,506 --> 00:11:48,133
They used their hands

147
00:11:48,374 --> 00:11:49,705
and stone implements to live

148
00:11:49,943 --> 00:11:53,243
for thousands of years.

149
00:12:38,791 --> 00:12:40,418
During the late glacial period

150
00:12:40,827 --> 00:12:43,421
temperatures began to rise.

151
00:12:43,663 --> 00:12:45,654
Sea levels also continued to rise.

152
00:12:46,165 --> 00:12:48,190
Some 10,000 years ago,

153
00:12:48,434 --> 00:12:50,528
the land bridge between Taiwan and

154
00:12:50,770 --> 00:12:52,829
the mainland became submerged.

155
00:12:53,072 --> 00:12:54,369
Taiwan thus became

156
00:12:54,607 --> 00:12:57,508
an isolated island.

157
00:13:22,135 --> 00:13:25,230
The Formosan Landlocked
Salmons in Tachia River

158
00:13:26,005 --> 00:13:28,997
first appeared off the sea of Japan.

159
00:13:29,842 --> 00:13:32,004
Between 800,000 to 100,000 years ago,

160
00:13:32,512 --> 00:13:35,709
temperature dropped rapidly
during the glacial period,

161
00:13:36,282 --> 00:13:36,942
and salmons migrated southward

162
00:13:37,183 --> 00:13:39,811
to the rivers of Taiwan.

163
00:13:49,162 --> 00:13:50,789
At the end of the glacial period,

164
00:13:51,297 --> 00:13:52,594
temperature rose,

165
00:13:53,132 --> 00:13:54,327
and the salmons became trapped

166
00:13:54,567 --> 00:13:56,467
in the cool-water rivers
in Taiwan's high mountains.

167
00:13:56,703 --> 00:13:58,296
They have survived to the present

168
00:13:59,472 --> 00:14:00,234
and evolved to become

169
00:14:00,473 --> 00:14:02,601
a species unique to Taiwan.

170
00:14:02,842 --> 00:14:03,468
Isolation caused species

171
00:14:03,710 --> 00:14:07,078
to undergo fascinating evolution.

172
00:14:09,515 --> 00:14:10,482
Glaciers

173
00:14:10,717 --> 00:14:11,275
also brought various flora

174
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:14,179
to Taiwan.

175
00:14:14,921 --> 00:14:17,253
Some 1.5 million years ago,

176
00:14:17,490 --> 00:14:19,424
the first cypress trees from the north

177
00:14:19,659 --> 00:14:22,128
thrived in Taiwan.

178
00:14:24,864 --> 00:14:26,093
Five hundred thousand years later,

179
00:14:26,332 --> 00:14:28,824
a large number of Fagaceae
appeared on the island,

180
00:14:33,106 --> 00:14:33,732
followed by

181
00:14:33,973 --> 00:14:36,840
broad-leaved trees.

182
00:14:41,147 --> 00:14:42,706
One hundred thousand years ago,

183
00:14:42,949 --> 00:14:44,713
Pinaceae trees began to appear

184
00:14:44,951 --> 00:14:47,852
and compete with broad-leaved trees.

185
00:14:51,324 --> 00:14:52,655
Ten thousand years later,

186
00:14:52,892 --> 00:14:54,417
climate change,

187
00:14:54,660 --> 00:14:57,391
ocean current, and birds

188
00:14:58,631 --> 00:15:00,895
brought tropical plants from the South

189
00:15:01,134 --> 00:15:03,569
into Taiwan.

190
00:15:05,371 --> 00:15:06,463
Isolation

191
00:15:06,706 --> 00:15:08,470
enabled the local fauna to be

192
00:15:08,708 --> 00:15:12,736
unique and vivacious.

193
00:16:02,361 --> 00:16:03,556
At the end of the glacial period,

194
00:16:03,796 --> 00:16:05,264
sea level rose and

195
00:16:05,631 --> 00:16:06,291
inundated areas

196
00:16:06,532 --> 00:16:09,024
inhabited by humans.

197
00:16:09,368 --> 00:16:10,961
When Noah was said to have built the Arc,

198
00:16:11,204 --> 00:16:14,469
and when flood stories were popular,

199
00:16:15,107 --> 00:16:17,439
people from south of the Asian continent

200
00:16:17,677 --> 00:16:19,736
and Indo-China

201
00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:21,640
might have

202
00:16:21,881 --> 00:16:23,042
used canoes

203
00:16:23,282 --> 00:16:24,306
to cross the sea

204
00:16:24,550 --> 00:16:26,348
and arrive at the western coast of Taiwan.

205
00:16:26,586 --> 00:16:30,352
A whirl of dusty wind sweeps beach.

206
00:16:30,523 --> 00:16:38,362
The splashing waves rise as high
as a building.

207
00:20:29,895 --> 00:20:31,226
Once, they buried a dog

208
00:20:31,464 --> 00:20:33,956
that had lived with them for a long time.

209
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:36,290
The dog, buried thousands of years ago,

210
00:20:36,535 --> 00:20:37,366
proves that

211
00:21:38,764 --> 00:21:40,289
which imprinted rope designs

212
00:21:40,533 --> 00:21:42,331
on the surface of ceramic implements.

213
00:21:52,211 --> 00:21:53,076
During the Neolithic Age,

214
00:21:53,312 --> 00:21:55,076
the early Tapenkeng culture

215
00:21:55,314 --> 00:21:55,837
subsequently evolved into

216
00:21:56,081 --> 00:21:59,210
cultures of the intermediate
and later periods,

217
00:22:02,788 --> 00:22:06,918
such as the Yuanshan,
Peinan, and Chilin cultures.

218
00:22:07,159 --> 00:22:10,390
There were also spiritual creations.

219
00:22:11,030 --> 00:22:13,431
The rope-design ceramics

220
00:22:13,666 --> 00:22:15,862
evolved into more beautiful

221
00:22:16,101 --> 00:22:19,332
and intricate thread-design ceramics.

222
00:22:51,503 --> 00:22:54,063
This is Yuanshan 3000 years ago.

223
00:22:54,740 --> 00:22:55,866
In the famous War at Muyeh

224
00:22:56,108 --> 00:22:57,974
in Chinese history,

225
00:22:59,245 --> 00:23:01,543
when Emperor Wu battled
against Emperor Chou

226
00:23:01,780 --> 00:23:04,010
and established the Chou Dynasty,

227
00:23:06,752 --> 00:23:09,221
migrants from the Asian continent

228
00:23:09,455 --> 00:23:10,786
arrived at the dense forest

229
00:23:11,023 --> 00:23:13,924
and animal-infested areas
along Tamsui bank.

230
00:23:34,914 --> 00:23:36,712
There they met the latter-period

231
00:23:36,949 --> 00:23:39,475
Tapenkeng people who
had settled along river bank.

232
00:23:48,861 --> 00:23:49,851
To avoid confrontation

233
00:23:50,095 --> 00:23:52,621
with the Tapenkeng people
across the river,

234
00:23:52,865 --> 00:23:54,230
the new migrants

235
00:23:54,466 --> 00:23:56,400
chose to leave.

236
00:23:56,669 --> 00:24:00,071
They moved inland, settling
by a lake at Yuanshan Island.

237
00:24:42,348 --> 00:24:44,908
They depended on the rich

238
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:47,380
resources in the lake for livelihood.

239
00:24:48,387 --> 00:24:51,755
These were the Yuanshan culture people.

240
00:25:16,482 --> 00:25:18,780
They harvested shellfish for food.

241
00:25:19,018 --> 00:25:19,849
The discarded shells were piled in pits

242
00:25:20,085 --> 00:25:21,985
and buried underground,

243
00:25:22,221 --> 00:25:25,953
forming what archeologists
today call the shell mound.

244
00:26:19,211 --> 00:26:20,610
Also, 3000 years ago,

245
00:26:20,846 --> 00:26:22,712
in Peinan plains of Taitung

246
00:26:23,916 --> 00:26:26,214
lived the Peinan culture people.

247
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:42,827
They took a different path

248
00:26:43,068 --> 00:26:45,036
in their pursuit for beauty.

249
00:26:46,438 --> 00:26:49,703
The Peinan people loved ornaments.

250
00:26:50,843 --> 00:26:52,004
Their favorite ornaments

251
00:26:52,244 --> 00:26:56,078
were jade earrings, porcelain bracelets,

252
00:26:56,315 --> 00:26:58,909
and jade arm bands.

253
00:28:39,218 --> 00:28:40,708
The Peinan people buried

254
00:28:40,953 --> 00:28:43,081
their dead at home

255
00:28:43,322 --> 00:28:45,484
to symbolize the coexistence

256
00:28:45,724 --> 00:28:47,021
and companionship of the dead

257
00:28:47,259 --> 00:28:49,591
and their living relatives.

258
00:28:50,729 --> 00:28:52,697
They laid the remains horizontally,

259
00:28:52,931 --> 00:28:55,628
and put jade earrings
with human-animal designs

260
00:28:55,867 --> 00:28:58,996
along side the body as burial objects.

261
00:29:07,045 --> 00:29:09,104
These jade ornaments

262
00:29:09,348 --> 00:29:10,816
became the key symbol

263
00:29:11,049 --> 00:29:13,450
of the Peinan culture people.

264
00:29:14,753 --> 00:29:15,743
This design might be

265
00:29:15,988 --> 00:29:18,252
a fad or be popular

266
00:29:18,490 --> 00:29:21,152
among people in the past.

267
00:29:44,182 --> 00:29:47,675
Similar artifacts were also found

268
00:29:48,220 --> 00:29:50,052
in the Wanshan ruins in Yilan and

269
00:29:50,289 --> 00:29:51,620
the Yuanshan ruins in Taipei.

270
00:29:51,857 --> 00:29:53,552
They show that during ancient times,

271
00:29:53,792 --> 00:29:54,987
there might have been close contacts

272
00:29:55,227 --> 00:29:57,924
between people living in
different areas islandwide.

273
00:30:13,011 --> 00:30:14,103
Peinan culture people

274
00:30:14,346 --> 00:30:16,405
buried their dead

275
00:30:16,648 --> 00:30:19,811
with the feet facing Tulan mountain,

276
00:30:21,153 --> 00:30:22,587
which was holy to the

277
00:30:22,821 --> 00:30:24,448
Peinan culture people.

278
00:30:27,159 --> 00:30:28,183
They believed that,

279
00:30:28,427 --> 00:30:29,724
this way, the dead

280
00:30:29,961 --> 00:30:32,589
would have real peace.

281
00:30:51,917 --> 00:30:53,112
To mankind,

282
00:30:53,352 --> 00:30:54,717
the sea is both an obstacle

283
00:30:54,953 --> 00:30:56,250
and a passageway.

284
00:30:57,155 --> 00:30:59,647
Those who had overcome
Hardships to arrive here

285
00:30:59,891 --> 00:31:03,054
might set sail to far places
to fulfill their dreams.

286
00:31:05,630 --> 00:31:07,758
Some historians and linguists believe

287
00:31:07,999 --> 00:31:10,559
Taiwan is the origin of Austronesian.

288
00:31:12,137 --> 00:31:14,231
Some 5000 years ago,

289
00:31:14,473 --> 00:31:16,805
a group of people from Taiwan

290
00:31:17,042 --> 00:31:19,636
traveled south to the Philippines.

291
00:31:26,618 --> 00:31:28,643
Some 4,500 years ago,

292
00:31:28,887 --> 00:31:31,515
they proceeded west to the north

293
00:31:31,757 --> 00:31:33,725
of Borneo, finally arriving
at Sulawesi in Indonesia.

294
00:31:35,427 --> 00:31:36,656
Timor.

295
00:31:36,895 --> 00:31:39,227
Settlers arrived at Sumatra 4000 years ago.

296
00:31:39,464 --> 00:31:40,761
They arrived at Java

297
00:31:43,969 --> 00:31:45,334
3600 years ago.

298
00:31:45,570 --> 00:31:48,062
They arrived
at northern coast of New Guinea

299
00:31:48,306 --> 00:31:50,866
and the stretch of land
along the southeastern coast.

300
00:31:55,914 --> 00:31:58,042
The population rapidly spread,

301
00:31:58,417 --> 00:32:01,011
moving to the east of Solomon Islands,

302
00:32:01,253 --> 00:32:03,415
the Pacific Ocean where
no man had ever set foot.

303
00:32:03,655 --> 00:32:04,850
Some 1000 years ago,

304
00:32:05,090 --> 00:32:05,648
all the inhabitable islands

305
00:32:05,891 --> 00:32:07,950
in Oceania

306
00:32:08,193 --> 00:32:10,184
were occupied by settlers.

307
00:32:10,862 --> 00:32:13,923
They then moved west along
the northern coast of Indian

308
00:32:14,166 --> 00:32:17,625
Ocean, arriving at Madagascar
at Africa's east coast.

309
00:32:26,545 --> 00:32:28,912
Legend of the Tawu tribe in Lanyu tells

310
00:32:29,147 --> 00:32:32,310
of ancestors from the southern islands,

311
00:32:32,551 --> 00:32:34,645
who traveled to and from the islands

312
00:32:34,886 --> 00:32:36,820
for a long period of time.

313
00:32:37,055 --> 00:32:39,524
They engaged in trade and intermarriage.

314
00:32:55,907 --> 00:32:58,376
This mobile lifestyle depicts

315
00:32:58,610 --> 00:32:59,338
possible traces of development

316
00:32:59,511 --> 00:33:03,038
and migration of the Austronesian.

317
00:33:39,017 --> 00:33:40,280
If Austronesian originated from Taiwan

318
00:33:40,519 --> 00:33:43,386
5000 years ago

319
00:33:43,622 --> 00:33:46,182
and migrated to the Pacific islands,

320
00:33:46,725 --> 00:33:47,954
then within this

321
00:33:48,193 --> 00:33:49,627
4000 to 5000 years and aided

322
00:33:49,861 --> 00:33:51,727
by the climate and ocean current,

323
00:33:51,963 --> 00:33:54,432
other Austronesian from the South

324
00:33:54,666 --> 00:33:57,328
could also have migrated to Taiwan.

325
00:33:58,937 --> 00:34:00,063
At different times,

326
00:34:00,305 --> 00:34:02,205
there were different peoples

327
00:34:02,440 --> 00:34:03,805
who came and left,

328
00:34:04,042 --> 00:34:06,670
which contributed to the
complex culture in Taiwan.

329
00:34:09,247 --> 00:34:12,148
To the later immigrants
from mainland China,

330
00:34:12,384 --> 00:34:15,479
Taiwan was a hew home.

331
00:34:15,787 --> 00:34:17,983
To Austronesian,

332
00:34:18,957 --> 00:34:22,393
Taiwan was a starting point
of their southward migration.

333
00:34:24,095 --> 00:34:25,358
The coming and going of peoples

334
00:34:25,597 --> 00:34:26,723
facilitated historical development

335
00:34:26,965 --> 00:34:29,332
in Taiwan.

336
00:34:31,002 --> 00:34:32,868
The stories started and finished

337
00:34:33,104 --> 00:34:35,471
on the island.

338
00:35:21,186 --> 00:35:22,051
Isolated by the sea

339
00:35:22,287 --> 00:35:24,813
and screened off by mountains,

340
00:35:25,290 --> 00:35:28,260
Austronesian who arrived
during different periods

341
00:35:28,493 --> 00:35:31,087
developed their own unique civilizations.

342
00:35:31,796 --> 00:35:33,855
On this beautiful island,

343
00:35:34,099 --> 00:35:36,397
they maintained their unique customs,
traditions,

344
00:35:36,635 --> 00:35:38,364
arts, and beliefs.

345
00:35:44,976 --> 00:35:47,308
Yet the subsequent rulers that arrived,

346
00:35:47,545 --> 00:35:49,070
in order to facilitate governance,

347
00:35:49,314 --> 00:35:50,076
classified the natives
as “raw” and “cultured”

348
00:35:50,315 --> 00:35:53,114
based on their familiarity
with Chinese culture

349
00:35:53,351 --> 00:35:56,582
and geography.

350
00:35:56,821 --> 00:36:00,519
The rulers then called them
mountain and plain dwellers.

351
00:36:00,892 --> 00:36:02,860
Fact is,
the peoples of Taiwan were far more

352
00:36:03,094 --> 00:36:05,586
complicated
than the categorization suggests.

353
00:36:10,068 --> 00:36:11,092
We are uncertain whether

354
00:36:11,336 --> 00:36:13,805
those who lived during the Neolithic Age

355
00:36:14,039 --> 00:36:15,837
and in the different culture areas

356
00:36:16,074 --> 00:36:19,442
were ancestors of the mountain dwellers.

357
00:36:21,846 --> 00:36:23,245
Their lifestyles,

358
00:36:23,481 --> 00:36:24,710
nevertheless,

359
00:36:24,949 --> 00:36:27,077
showed similarities.

360
00:36:27,952 --> 00:36:29,784
For instance, 2700 years ago,

361
00:36:30,021 --> 00:36:31,546
the people living in Tamalin,

362
00:36:31,790 --> 00:36:33,622
came from the eastern coast.

363
00:36:33,858 --> 00:36:36,452
They migrated upstream Choshui River

364
00:36:36,695 --> 00:36:39,960
and settled in the mountains
923 meters above sea level.

365
00:36:51,576 --> 00:36:54,705
They were later referred to
as the Chu-ping people.

366
00:36:55,814 --> 00:36:57,043
We don't know if they were ancestors of

367
00:36:57,282 --> 00:37:00,149
the Bunun or Atayal people,

368
00:37:00,952 --> 00:37:03,387
but their houses were build

369
00:37:03,621 --> 00:37:06,750
the same way as the Bunun's.

370
00:37:14,799 --> 00:37:17,791
The headhunting custom

371
00:37:18,036 --> 00:37:19,800
of the Austronesian
was also similar to that of

372
00:37:20,038 --> 00:37:21,699
Yuanshan culture people who
lived in the Taipei basin.

373
00:37:21,940 --> 00:37:24,409
From Austronesian legends and songs,

374
00:37:24,642 --> 00:37:26,201
there are evidences of their continuing

375
00:37:26,444 --> 00:37:28,674
migration on land.

376
00:37:29,481 --> 00:37:32,212
(Atayal dialect by the tribal chief)

377
00:37:32,450 --> 00:37:35,181
I'll tell you today's topic.

378
00:37:35,420 --> 00:37:36,854
It's about ancient traditional customs.

379
00:37:37,088 --> 00:37:40,251
About how the Atayals migrated.

380
00:37:40,492 --> 00:37:43,655
I will use ancient poems to tell the story.

381
00:37:43,795 --> 00:37:46,924
Uncle Temu, I'll begin.

382
00:37:47,298 --> 00:37:53,829
Allow me to look for

383
00:37:54,072 --> 00:37:58,908
a place to reflect.

384
00:37:59,144 --> 00:38:03,980
This is not a serious matter.

385
00:38:04,215 --> 00:38:10,313
Come, let us chat.

386
00:38:13,091 --> 00:38:14,081
(Ancient Atayal teachings)

387
00:38:14,325 --> 00:38:17,351
Ah!

388
00:38:20,064 --> 00:38:25,264
The ancestral home of the Atayals.

389
00:38:26,638 --> 00:38:32,304
To seek prosperity for our tribe,
three brothers

390
00:38:32,544 --> 00:38:43,478
ventured north.

391
00:38:44,088 --> 00:38:48,650
Buta went to Taoyuan and Hsinchu.

392
00:38:48,893 --> 00:38:52,852
Ayen went to Yilan.

393
00:38:53,097 --> 00:39:00,333
Yabox went to Nantou and Taichung.

394
00:39:00,572 --> 00:39:06,443
Before leaving, they made a promise

395
00:39:06,678 --> 00:39:18,181
to not use wooden fences
to isolate one another.

396
00:39:18,423 --> 00:39:26,558
They would thrive like bamboo shoots.

397
00:39:37,442 --> 00:39:39,171
Some 1800 years ago,

398
00:39:39,410 --> 00:39:40,309
the earliest metallurgy appeared

399
00:39:40,545 --> 00:39:42,513
in northern Taiwan.

400
00:39:42,814 --> 00:39:45,749
It was unique and indigenous.

401
00:39:46,551 --> 00:39:47,848
These Shihsanhang culture people,

402
00:39:48,086 --> 00:39:49,417
who knew metallurgy,

403
00:39:49,654 --> 00:39:50,746
might be the ancestors of the

404
00:39:50,989 --> 00:39:52,354
plain-dwelling Ketagalan

405
00:39:52,590 --> 00:39:55,525
in northern and northeastern Taiwan.

406
00:40:32,864 --> 00:40:36,129
They collected iron sand
along the coast of Pali,

407
00:40:38,670 --> 00:40:41,901
and set up workshop near the lagoon.

408
00:40:42,140 --> 00:40:44,768
They introduced iron sand
and fuel separately into

409
00:40:45,009 --> 00:40:48,468
furnaces made of stones
and mud from the lagoon.

410
00:40:49,580 --> 00:40:52,345
They struck the metal repeatedly

411
00:40:52,984 --> 00:40:54,645
and polished the metal.

412
00:40:55,019 --> 00:40:57,852
The daily metallic implement used by the

413
00:40:58,089 --> 00:40:59,887
Shihsanhang culture people
was how finished.

414
00:41:10,935 --> 00:41:12,960
Because iron sand contains titanium,

415
00:41:13,204 --> 00:41:15,172
the quality of the products was poor.

416
00:41:16,607 --> 00:41:18,200
Taiwan's Iron Age was

417
00:41:18,443 --> 00:41:20,605
1200 to 1600 years behind

418
00:41:20,845 --> 00:41:24,145
those of Europe and China.

419
00:41:24,382 --> 00:41:26,714
Taiwan's civilization, however,

420
00:41:26,951 --> 00:41:28,612
skipped the Bronze Age,

421
00:41:29,220 --> 00:41:30,051
and jumped directly from
the Stone Age

422
00:41:30,288 --> 00:41:32,723
into the Iron Age.

423
00:41:38,930 --> 00:41:40,193
During the 15th century

424
00:41:40,431 --> 00:41:42,365
when Chengho sailed the oceans,

425
00:41:42,667 --> 00:41:45,159
the Shihsanhang culture people

426
00:41:45,403 --> 00:41:48,805
already knew how to trade sulfur
and deer hide

427
00:41:49,040 --> 00:41:51,702
for Chinese porcelain bowls,

428
00:41:51,943 --> 00:41:53,843
salt, and textiles with

429
00:41:54,078 --> 00:41:57,070
traders from the Ming Dynasty.

430
00:41:58,082 --> 00:41:58,708
This might be the beginning of

431
00:41:58,950 --> 00:42:01,942
external economic activities in Taiwan..

432
00:42:13,131 --> 00:42:14,758
Compared with mountain dwellers,

433
00:42:14,999 --> 00:42:16,763
plain-dwellers were more
diverse and complicated.

434
00:42:17,168 --> 00:42:18,658
Their ancestors were Austronesian who

435
00:42:18,903 --> 00:42:21,873
arrived very early in Taiwan.

436
00:42:22,306 --> 00:42:23,273
Most settled in the

437
00:42:23,508 --> 00:42:27,172
western and eastern coastal plains.

438
00:42:27,445 --> 00:42:30,779
Burning forest for farming,
they fished and hunted.

439
00:42:59,944 --> 00:43:02,106
Before the 16th and 17th centuries,

440
00:43:02,780 --> 00:43:03,645
before their frequent contact

441
00:43:03,881 --> 00:43:06,009
with the Han people,

442
00:43:06,250 --> 00:43:07,581
their life and customs were

443
00:43:07,819 --> 00:43:10,845
pure to their culture.

444
00:43:13,724 --> 00:43:16,455
Some plain-dwellers lived
in maternal societies

445
00:43:16,694 --> 00:43:19,595
where women were responsible
for agriculture,

446
00:43:22,834 --> 00:43:24,893
while men were responsible for hunting.

447
00:43:26,537 --> 00:43:27,732
The men would bring their dogs,

448
00:43:27,972 --> 00:43:29,701
bow and arrows, and blowguns

449
00:43:29,974 --> 00:43:32,341
to hunt for deer and boars in groups,

450
00:43:32,577 --> 00:43:35,103
or fish in the rivers.

451
00:43:35,480 --> 00:43:36,606
The River of Time

452
00:43:36,848 --> 00:43:39,476
has engulfed ancient civilizations.

453
00:43:39,750 --> 00:43:41,980
Heavily influenced by the Han culture,

454
00:43:42,220 --> 00:43:45,850
most of their traditional customs and
mother tongue became lost.

455
00:44:01,339 --> 00:44:02,568
In 1544,

456
00:44:02,807 --> 00:44:04,502
a Portuguese ship

457
00:44:04,742 --> 00:44:06,232
set sail from Macao

458
00:44:06,477 --> 00:44:08,070
to cross the Taiwan Strait.

459
00:44:08,312 --> 00:44:11,441
The ship's destination was Japan.

460
00:44:24,428 --> 00:44:25,657
The 16th century was a time

461
00:44:25,897 --> 00:44:28,059
of great geographic discoveries.

462
00:44:28,466 --> 00:44:31,231
Armed with cannons and strong ships,

463
00:44:31,469 --> 00:44:33,267
Westerners sailed all over the world.

464
00:44:33,804 --> 00:44:36,569
They opened opportunities
for cultural interaction.

465
00:44:36,807 --> 00:44:39,401
They also gave a beautiful

466
00:44:39,644 --> 00:44:41,806
name to an island in the East.

467
00:44:48,319 --> 00:44:52,278
Terra (land).

468
00:45:05,403 --> 00:45:06,837
Terra (land).

469
00:45:07,305 --> 00:45:09,000
Terra (land).

470
00:45:14,612 --> 00:45:16,171
Ilha Formosa (beautiful island)

471
00:45:16,414 --> 00:45:17,848
Ilha Formosa (beautiful island)

472
00:45:18,082 --> 00:45:21,245
Ilha Formosa (beautiful island)

473
00:45:28,192 --> 00:45:29,421
From then on, Taiwan,

474
00:45:29,660 --> 00:45:31,924
which was mostly Austronesian,

475
00:45:32,163 --> 00:45:33,722
became the beautiful

476
00:45:33,965 --> 00:45:37,060
island of Formosa to the Westerners.

477
00:46:06,731 --> 00:46:09,359
Things changed rapidly

478
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:11,090
with the advent of the 17th century.

479
00:46:11,535 --> 00:46:13,867
The quickened pace of change

480
00:46:14,105 --> 00:46:16,574
has dawned upon the island of Taiwan.

481
00:46:26,183 --> 00:46:28,174
Faced with superior Western sea power,

482
00:46:28,419 --> 00:46:29,409
Japanese pirates to the east,

483
00:46:29,654 --> 00:46:32,021
and contentions among trader groups,

484
00:46:32,290 --> 00:46:35,282
Taiwan started to emerge

485
00:46:35,526 --> 00:46:37,585
into the world scene.

